                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18121028-56-off310 t18121028-56-crimeloc313"></join>. On the 20th of October, about half after one, I was stooping down at my shop-window; I heard some one go across my shop, I lifted up my head, and saw the prisoner; he ran out of my shop. I pursued him, and brought him back. This is the leather I took from him. It is mine.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I have it to your mercy. It was entirely through distress I did it.</p>
               <p>GUILTY, aged 52,</p>
